.TH "ide_dma_map_sg" 9 "ide_dma_map_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ide_dma_map_sg \- map IDE scatter gather for DMA I/O
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ide_dma_map_sg
.BI "(ide_drive_t *drive "  ","
.BI "struct ide_cmd *cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drive" 12
the drive to map the DMA table for
.IP "cmd" 12
command

Perform the DMA mapping magic necessary to access the source or
target buffers of a request via DMA.  The lower layers of the
kernel provide the necessary cache management so that we can
operate in a portable fashion.
